<DOC><DOCNO> AP900428-0025 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-28-90 0450EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-PitBull-Brothers     04-28 0200</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Pit Bull-Brothers,0205</SECOND><HEAD>Boy Mauled By Same Dog Who Apparently Attacked Brother Two YearsAgo</HEAD><DATELINE>MIDDLETOWN, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A 2-year-old boy was in stablecondition after he was mauled by his family's pit bull, the samedog that apparently attacked his brother two years ago, authoritiessaid.   Bruce Scott Herrin suffered deep bites on his face, shouldersand chest when the pit bull, Kone, attacked him as they played intheir back yard on Thursday.   His mother, Athena Herrin, pulled the 90-pound animal off herson, carried the boy into the house, called rescue workers thenshot the dog to death, said Lake County Sheriff's Capt. GlenPerkins.   The boy underwent five hours of surgery Thursday night, and onFriday his condition was upgraded from extremely critical to stable.   In the summer of 1988, the dog apparently attacked BobbieHerrin, then 2, when the boy tried to hug the dog as it slept, saidDennis Burke, Lake County animal control officer. The boy sufferedcuts and a fractured skull when his head hit the table.   The dog then was locked up until an investigator reported thatKone was calm and friendly and showed no signs of aggressivebehavior.</TEXT></DOC>